Group ride (no-drop) Biking with Baddies Monthly Sunday rides, Women only Instagram, Website.

Last Sunday of every month. 2:00 PM

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
items.location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

When: Friday Nov 28, 2025 4:00 PM. Roll at 4:30 pm. 

Start and Finish: Fulton Beer Taproom Mid-ride stop: Bohemian Flats Park

🍻 Return: Fulton Beer, where every rider gets a free drink (beer, THC beverage, or NA option)

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Schlöpptoberween Volume 6. Facebook.

When: Saturday Nov 15, 2025 10:00 AM

Start: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop. 

Distance: 20-30 miles. Pace: 10-12 mph. 

An annual fundraiser ride hitting bandit trails around the city, with regular stops to hit jumps or fun trail features. Bring a dirt-capable bike (a gravel bike is fine, a mountain bike or fat bike will be more fun). Includes a raffle with great prizes as a fundraiser for Pedal Power MN. 

Costumes are encouraged and this year is sports themed. “SPORTS can take many shapes so start making a game-plan for your fit for the day. Any SPORT or SPORTS adjacent theme is probably a good place to start. But DO NOT SHOW UP AS A REF OR UMP OR OFFICIAL OR ZEBRA unless you chat with Comissioner Ders.”
items.location: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop, 208 13th Ave NE, Minneapolis, MN 55413, USA

items.description:
Race (alleycat) St. Paul Cranksgiving. Event page. 

Saturday Nov 22, 2025 12:00 PM. Manifests 12:30 pm, 1pm roll-out, 4pm cut-off. 

Start: 1697 Lafond Avenue (Zion Lutheran Church, St. Paul)

This is a food drive where folks ride bicycles to bring food and sundries to donate to Zion Lutheran Church in St. Paul’s Midway neighborhood.

Zion Lutheran Church operates a weekly food ministry that provides food and sundries to the needy. Mr. Michael Recycles Bicycles partners with Zion Lutheran annually to conduct a bicycle powered food drive where people bring their food and sundry donations by bicycle to the event.

People can participate 3 ways:

  • Carry donations to Zion Lutheran Church by bicycle on November 22 between noon and 4 PM

  • Participate in the alley-cat style race to purchase food items at local stores

  • Call 651-641-1037 to arrange an appointment to have someone pick up food items from their home by bicycle (available only for people living in the Hamline Midway neighborhood)
items.location: 1697 Lafond Ave, St Paul, MN 55104, USA

items.description:
Race (alleycat) Out and Back Relay. Instagram. 

When: Friday Nov 21, 2025 6:00 PM. 6:30pm race. 

Start: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge

RULES: you must have a team of at max 3 to compete 4 laps from sabo ->cedar south beach.

Don’t have more people? Just comment that you’re looking for a team!! Don’t be afraid to say hi. Want to volunteer? Hmu i need a beach bitch

We will be stationed on the bridge so you can stash your bags and warm layers etc. Sabo is windy. Plan accordingly. Afters at eagles.
items.location: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge, Minneapolis, MN 55407, USA

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Holiday Decor Hauling Ride Instagram, Website

When: Saturday Dec 6, 2025 9:45 AM. Roll at 10am.

Start and Finish: Garden of Hope and Healing (420 Cedar Lake Rd S)

Distance: ~3 miles round trip. Pace: 8-10 mph. 

Join the Bryn Mawr Active Transportation Committee for a ~3 mile winter bike ride to the Minneapolis Farmers Market to pick up holiday decor. Wreaths, garlands, and even trees will be available for purchase - and we will transport them back to Bryn Mawr in a car-free manner! Bring a trailer (if you have one).

Feel free to reach out on Instagram at @activetransit.brynmawr or send us an email at activetransit-brynmawr@googlegroups.com.

items.description:
Race (alleycat) A Few Gears Eve. Instagram. 

When: Wednesday Dec 31, 2025 7:00 PM. Reg opens at 7pm, 7:45pm roll-out to secret start.

Start: Spot Bar (859 Randolph Ave, St. Paul)

Cost: Entry is $20 suggested donation, which will go 100% to Second Harvest Heartland. 

The fourteenth version of Saint Paul's longest running alley cat is back and better than ever!

For the race you'll need a bike, a pen, bike lights, your device, warm clothes, a backpack, money for drinks, curiosity, a playful attitude and a sense of wonder.  

The race will be no more than 20 miles with the proper number of hills to keep everyone warm. 

There is no requirement to drink alcohol, only to support the checkpoint hosting establishment. 

There will be prizes for the top finishers in three categories: Open, Women, and Gender Non Conforming.  There will also be a prize for DFL. 

After party with food, drink, sauna and a bonfire.
items.location: Spot Bar, 859 Randolph Ave, St Paul, MN 55102, USA
